        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "xvDbM",
          "name": "Paul Story",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "gap": 80,
          "padding": [
            100,
            120
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "rSafL",
              "name": "storyPhoto",
              "metadata": {
                "type": "unsplash",
                "username": "tanyabarrow",
                "link": "https://unsplash.com/@tanyabarrow",
                "author": "Tanya Barrow"
              },
              "width": 480,
              "height": 580,
              "fill": {
                "type": "image",
                "enabled": true,
                "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1762445333169-0c7d95a5e6c0?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&ixid=M3w4NDM0ODN8MHwxfHJhbmRvbXx8fHx8fHx8fDE3NzIyNjA5NzJ8&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&q=80&w=1080",
                "mode": "fill"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "P2OMJ",
              "name": "storyText",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 28,
              "justifyContent": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "TcYTt",
                  "name": "storyLabel",
                  "fill": "$burnt-orange",
                  "content": "PAUL'S STORY",
                  "fontFamily": "Barlow Semi Condensed",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 3
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "PTc6g",
                  "name": "storyTitle",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "content": "From Grief to Purpose",
                  "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                  "fontSize": 42,
                  "fontWeight": "600",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "YlesI",
                  "name": "storyDivider",
                  "width": 60,
                  "height": 3,
                  "fill": "$burnt-orange"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "I5EwD",
                  "name": "storyP1",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "In 2023, I lost my mother to pancreatic cancer. Just fourteen months later, my father was diagnosed with lung cancer. He passed away in early 2025. In the span of two years, cancer took both of my parents from me.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Punnw",
                  "name": "storyP2",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The grief was overwhelming. But somewhere in that darkness, I found a spark of purpose. I realized that while I couldn't change what happened to my parents, I could help others — by raising awareness about cancer prevention and the lifestyle choices that can reduce risk.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "oCS8V",
                  "name": "storyP3",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "So in March 2026, I'm lacing up my boots and walking the entire Pacific Crest Trail — 2,650 miles from the Mexican border to Canada — to honor my parents and raise funds for cancer research and prevention programs.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "ynm8s",
          "name": "Quote Section",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "$bg-dark",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 24,
          "padding": [
            80,
            200
          ],
          "alignItems": "center",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "1vruQ",
              "name": "quoteIcon",
              "fill": "$burnt-orange",
              "content": "“",
              "lineHeight": 0.5,
              "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
              "fontSize": 120,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "87piK",
              "name": "quoteText",
              "fill": "#FFFFFFCC",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 800,
              "content": "Every mile I walk is a mile closer to a world where fewer families have to say goodbye too soon. This trail is my protest against cancer — one step at a time.",
              "lineHeight": 1.7,
              "textAlign": "center",
              "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
              "fontSize": 28,
              "fontWeight": "normal",
              "fontStyle": "italic"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "ZxDXY",
              "name": "quoteAttr",
              "fill": "$burnt-orange",
              "content": "— Paul Barry",
              "fontFamily": "Barlow Semi Condensed",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "600",
              "letterSpacing": 2
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "kJCyj",
          "name": "Prevention Section",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "$bg-white",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 60,
          "padding": [
            100,
            120
          ],
          "alignItems": "center",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "PozES",
              "name": "preventHeader",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 16,
              "alignItems": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "99gJf",
                  "name": "preventLabel",
                  "fill": "$burnt-orange",
                  "content": "CANCER PREVENTION",
                  "fontFamily": "Barlow Semi Condensed",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 3
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "vd7fT",
                  "name": "preventTitle",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "content": "Prevention Starts With Lifestyle",
                  "textAlign": "center",
                  "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                  "fontSize": 42,
                  "fontWeight": "600",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "fkst3",
                  "name": "preventSub",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": 700,
                  "content": "Research shows that up to 50% of cancers could be prevented through healthy lifestyle choices. Here are the habits that can make a real difference.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "textAlign": "center",
                  "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "WjPiD",
              "name": "tipsGrid",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "gap": 32,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "TJVF6",
                  "name": "tip1",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$bg-card",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 20,
                  "padding": 32,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "icon_font",
                      "id": "eq0M2",
                      "name": "tip1Icon",
                      "width": 32,
                      "height": 32,
                      "iconFontName": "footprints",
                      "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                      "fill": "$forest-green"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "rmyUG",
                      "name": "tip1Title",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "content": "Stay Active",
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "W8Pvp",
                      "name": "tip1Desc",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Regular physical activity reduces risk for several cancers including colon, breast, and lung cancer. Even 30 minutes of daily walking makes a difference.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "Yl7ig",
                  "name": "tip2",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$bg-card",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 20,
                  "padding": 32,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "icon_font",
                      "id": "dF5ME",
                      "name": "tip2Icon",
                      "width": 32,
                      "height": 32,
                      "iconFontName": "apple",
                      "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                      "fill": "$forest-green"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "xnSpU",
                      "name": "tip2Title",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "content": "Eat Well",
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "1lRdA",
                      "name": "tip2Desc",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "A diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains while limiting processed meats and alcohol can significantly lower cancer risk. Nourish your body.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "RhLrL",
                  "name": "tip3",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$bg-card",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 20,
                  "padding": 32,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "icon_font",
                      "id": "eb8uU",
                      "name": "tip3Icon",
                      "width": 32,
                      "height": 32,
                      "iconFontName": "sun",
                      "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                      "fill": "$forest-green"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "78G7g",
                      "name": "tip3Title",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "content": "Sun Safety",
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "EsW7y",
                      "name": "tip3Desc",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Protect your skin from UV radiation. Use sunscreen, wear protective clothing, and avoid tanning beds. Skin cancer is the most common but also one of the most preventable.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "JgkUL",
              "name": "tipsGrid2",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "gap": 32,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "kfR65",
                  "name": "tip4",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$bg-card",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 20,
                  "padding": 32,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "icon_font",
                      "id": "BIpk4",
                      "name": "tip4Icon",
                      "width": 32,
                      "height": 32,
                      "iconFontName": "scan-search",
                      "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                      "fill": "$forest-green"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "pjH6Z",
                      "name": "tip4Title",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "content": "Get Screened",
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "2afd6",
                      "name": "tip4Desc",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Regular screening can catch cancer early when it's most treatable. Talk to your doctor about recommended screenings for your age and risk factors.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "Q61cr",
                  "name": "tip5",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$bg-card",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 20,
                  "padding": 32,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "icon_font",
                      "id": "25Yu6",
                      "name": "tip5Icon",
                      "width": 32,
                      "height": 32,
                      "iconFontName": "cigarette-off",
                      "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                      "fill": "$forest-green"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "e2HUv",
                      "name": "tip5Title",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "content": "Quit Smoking",
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "X5xo8",
                      "name": "tip5Desc",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Tobacco use remains the single largest preventable cause of cancer. Quitting at any age reduces your risk. It's never too late to start.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "jDrQ8",
                  "name": "tip6",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$bg-card",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 20,
                  "padding": 32,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "icon_font",
                      "id": "AeqTn",
                      "name": "tip6Icon",
                      "width": 32,
                      "height": 32,
                      "iconFontName": "heart-pulse",
                      "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                      "fill": "$forest-green"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "IQEt1",
                      "name": "tip6Title",
                      "fill": "$text-primary",
                      "content": "Know Your Body",
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Ncyi2",
                      "name": "tip6Desc",
                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Pay attention to changes in your body. Unexplained weight loss, persistent pain, or unusual lumps should be discussed with a healthcare provider promptly.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Source Serif 4",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "nIhBX",
